This paper discusses the use of beamforming techniques to improve the performance of a MIMO system with a low precision ADC, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also considers the use of eigenmode power allocation, which is a control theory concept (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper uses simulation results to evaluate the performance of the proposed approach, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG) applications.
